<div class="content">
	<p>There are already a plethora of software licenses that a prospective cloud software developer and user must sort through.  Why on earth would we want to add another one to the mix? </p>

	<div class="section">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<h2><i class="fa fa-door-open"></i>Problems with Open Source</h2>
				<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_source" target="_blank">Open Source</a> licenses may be good for the code, but they are bad for the individual / developer.  Open Source licenses (as strictly defined by the <a href="https://opensource.org">Open Source Initiative</a>) require that the developer give up all rights to their work, which the tech giants proceed to monetize using their monopoly platforms and brands. By giving up their rights, developers are also giving up the possibilty of competing with the tech giants. </p>
			</div>
