	<div class="section">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<h2><i class="fa fa-door-closed"></i>Problems with Closed Source</h2>
				<p>The problems associated with Closed Source licenses are <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linus%27s_law">well documented</a>.  By keeping access to the source code closed, bugs remain hidden.  Since closed, proprietary software often requires  steep licensing fees, it tends to hurt the small, individual software user more than large corporate users who can more easily amortize and pass along the licensing costs.  Also, Closed Source software does not allow for the code to be expanded upon and for the ideas expressed in the code to proliferate and grow. </p>
			</div>
