	<div class="section">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<h2><i class="fa fa-hand-peace"></i>Problems with Ethical Source</h2>
				<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organization_for_Ethical_Source" target="_blank">Ethical Source</a> licenses are an attempt to address some of the shortcomings of the Open and Closed sourced licenses by stipulating how the software may be used.  The problem is that Ethical Source licenses are too vague. They tend to embrace ideas such as racial equity and environmental sustainability, which, while worthwhile goals, are not possible to define or enforce. So, while well-meaning, these licenses lack the specifics that would be required to make them legally binding. </p>
			</div>
