	<div class="section">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<h2><i class="fa fa-handshake"></i>Problems with Fair Source</h2>
				<p><a href="https://fair.io" target="_blank">Fair Source</a> licenses probably come the closest in spirit to the <%= application.name %> license by attempting to look out for the needs of the humans who develop and use the software. These licenses tend to allow individual use of the software but require a negotiation between the developer and the user for substantial commercial use.  Unfortunately, the tech community tends to find these restrictions too onerous and therefore tends to look down upon these licenses.  By stipulating a very small and specific set of restrictions, the <%= application.name %> license aims to overcome these objections. </p>
